<li id="cite_note-2"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-2">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">"FAIR originated as an internet-based group in the late 90s …. What happened was that there were religious discussions on the old AOL message boards, and the Mormons were getting pushed around. They were the 98 pound weaklings because they didn’t control the venue. The people that did, limited their access and things like that. So FAIR originated as a group of people banding together electronically for self defense." Kevin Barney, <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.fairlatterdaysaints.org/blog/2012/10/17/notes-on-apologetics/">Notes on Apologetics</a>, <i>FAIR Blog</i>, last modified 17 October 2012.</span>
